ZH: 我们的口语课程每周都会举行。
EN: Our spoken Chinese class is held every week.

ZH: 她的口语流利，几乎没有口音。
EN: Her spoken Chinese is fluent, with hardly any accent.

ZH: 我们需要多多练习口语才能提高。
EN: We need to practice speaking more in order to improve.

ZH: 他的口语能力比写作能力更强。
EN: His spoken language ability is stronger than his writing ability.

ZH: 我们可以通过和中国人交流来提高口语水平。
EN: We can improve our spoken Chinese by communicating with Chinese people.

ZH: 口语是汉语学习中的一个重要方面。
EN: Speaking is an important aspect of learning Chinese.

ZH: 我感觉自己的口语有点生疏了。
EN: I feel a little rusty in my spoken Chinese.

ZH: 在日常生活中，口语比书面语更常用。
EN: In daily life, spoken language is more commonly used than written language.

ZH: 他的口语表达清晰简洁。
EN: His spoken expression is clear and concise.

ZH: 她的口语能力让我们大吃一惊。
EN: Her spoken language ability surprised us.

ZH: 如果你想提高口语，多和中国人练习是最有效的方法。
EN: If you want to improve your spoken Chinese, practicing with Chinese people is the most effective method.

ZH: 在考试中要注意口语和听力的能力。
EN: Pay attention to your speaking and listening abilities in exams.

ZH: 口语交流是提高语言能力的好途径。
EN: Spoken communication is a good way to improve language skills.

ZH: 我们每周会有一次口语训练课。
EN: We have a spoken language training session once a week.

ZH: 学习口语要多听多说。
EN: To learn spoken Chinese, you need to listen and speak more.

ZH: 我们练习口语时需要做一些口语练习题。
EN: When practicing spoken Chinese, we need to do some speaking exercises.

ZH: 参加口语比赛是提高表达能力的好方法。
EN: Participating in a spoken language competition is a good way to improve expression skills.

ZH: 她每天早上会练习半个小时的口语。
EN: She practices spoken Chinese for half an hour every morning.

ZH: 在日常生活中，我们要多多练习口语。
EN: In daily life, we need to practice spoken Chinese more.

ZH: 提高口语需要不断地练习和积累。
EN: Improving spoken Chinese requires continuous practice and accumulation.
